<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09072i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09072i">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09072i"> 72(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> nerve of thoughts</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Des modifications particuli&egrave;res dues &agrave; la castration, la plus manifeste est sans contredit la perte de l&apos;&eacute;nergie morale. &hellip; &ldquo;Il semble, dit Virey, qu&apos;on ait coup&eacute; aux eunuques le nerf de la pens&eacute;e.&rdquo; <br><font color="green">[Of all the specific changes due to castration, the most patent is unquestionably the loss of moral energy.&hellip; Virey says that &ldquo;It seems that one had cut the nerve of thought in eunuchs&rdquo;.]</font> <small> Caufeynon, <a name="CAUF" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CAUF"><cite title="source">Les Monstres Humains</cite></a> (Paris, 1900) 102</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c03105e" href="c03all.htm#c03105e">VI.C.03:105(e)</a></mm></dd> </dd></dl>
